latestPosts.caption:
My Full Forearm Routine 👇🏻 
I start with bar forearm pushdowns these help isolate the forearms and really build that dense, vascular look. You don’t need to go too heavy, just focus on clean, controlled reps.

Then I move into heavy to moderate hammer curls. These aren’t just for the biceps they really help pack size and thickness into your forearms when done right, especially with a thumbless grip.

Lastly, I finish with reverse grip curls, one of the most underrated movements. These bring out the definition and target the outer forearm really well.

All three exercises are done thumbless, and I hit 3 sets of 8 to 10 reps, taken to complete failure.
